Ok,, I don't know the answer to this debate, but years ago, I used a
product called Delo from Chevron,

Then I found out from the list about the importance of knowing what your
doing,, and I asked the supplier if this product is ok in a VW transaxle

Of course, that is like asking the baker, Is the bread fresh?
They will always say "Sure is" just to make a sale.

That thought aside, he went on to describe the oil,, it is ok with yellow
metal syncro's... that is important.

One other thing I had experienced was foaming,,, some oils will foam,
create pressure in the trans,, and blow past the input shaft seal.. and
leak about a half cup all over the clutch, and the ground etc.

This Delo does not foam...

At first I worried about it,, but now I have driven just over 100,000kms
transmission is still intact, so I don't know If the lifespan has been
shortened

You can read about the oil with this PDF ... and see if it is available in
your area,, I was able to buy it in 1 quart bottles with a nice squirt lid
that allows you to put a hose on it, and squeeze it into the transmission.

http://www.globalserve.net/~jrivers/DELO%2080W90.pdf

